Mwendokasi Bus Ticket Booking System
Introduction

The Mwendokasi Bus Ticket Booking System is a web-based application developed to improve the bus ticket booking process by allowing passengers to book tickets online. Instead of standing in long queues or manually purchasing tickets, users can access the system through a web browser, select their destination, view ticket prices, generate tickets, and download or print them instantly.

This project was developed as an academic and practical learning project using web development technologies including HTML, CSS, JavaScript, PHP, and MySQL. The system demonstrates how technology can be used to improve public transportation services by making ticket booking faster, easier, and more convenient for passengers.

Purpose of the Project

The main purpose of this project is to provide a simple and efficient platform that allows passengers to book bus tickets online while enabling transport operators to manage bookings more effectively.

The system was designed to reduce manual work, improve record keeping, and provide passengers with a modern and user-friendly ticket booking experience.

Objectives
Main Objective

To develop a secure and user-friendly web application that enables online bus ticket booking and management.

Specific Objectives
To provide an online platform for bus ticket booking.
To display available routes and ticket prices.
To automatically calculate fares based on selected destinations.
To generate printable and downloadable tickets.
To provide multiple payment options for customers.
To allow customers to communicate with bus operators through various communication channels.
To store booking information securely in a database.
To improve customer satisfaction through efficient service delivery.

System Features
Home Page

The home page introduces users to the Mwendokasi Bus Services. It provides information about the company, available transportation services, bus facilities, and general advertisements encouraging customers to use the service.

The page also contains a slideshow displaying images of the buses, including both interior and exterior views, giving customers a better understanding of the transport services offered.

Route Page

The route page displays detailed information about available routes. Users can view:

Route names
Distance covered
Number of passengers allowed
Ticket prices
Route availability

The page also includes a map section that can later be extended to support real-time bus tracking.

Ticket Booking Page

This page allows customers to:

Enter personal information
Select a destination
Automatically view the ticket price
Select a preferred payment method
Generate a ticket
Print the ticket
Download the ticket as a PDF document
Contact Page

The contact page enables communication between customers and the transport company. It provides:

Phone numbers
Email addresses
WhatsApp contacts
Instagram account
X (Twitter) account

Customers can also submit comments and feedback regarding the services offered.

Ticket Generation

Once booking information is provided, the system automatically generates a ticket containing:

Passenger name
Phone number
Destination
Ticket price
Payment method
Booking date and time

The ticket can be printed or downloaded for future use.

Technologies Used

The project was developed using the following technologies:

Front-End Technologies
HTML5
CSS3
JavaScript
